feat(mfg-01): work-instruction source extractor template v1.0.0

Extracts manufacturing-critical facts from drawings, ECOs, planning
sheets, and process specs so a downstream copilot can draft shop-floor
work instructions:

  - critical features (KC, KPC, CSI, FlightSafetyCritical, FractureCritical)
  - tolerances (limit-dimensioning normalized to nominal/upper/lower)
  - fasteners with quantity, location, reuse rules, finish/plating
  - torque specs (value, tolerance, units, wet/dry, sequence, preload)
  - process specs (AMS, MIL, Nadcap) with revision and process_class
  - tooling, consumables, PPE, environmental controls
  - inspection / buyoff points with role
  - traceability requirements
  - ECO from/to deltas

Citation shape supports drawing zones (e.g. 'B4'), text sections, and
note IDs (e.g. 'NOTE 7'); each citation carries a source doc_id.

Runtime config:
  - Primitive=DocumentExtract, Temperature=0.0
  - DataSensitivityTier=ITAR
  - MinConfidenceThreshold=0.80 (shop-floor errors are safety-of-flight)
  - RefuseIfUngrounded enabled for torque_specs, tolerances,
    process_specs, fasteners — model must not invent values

Consumer: MFG-01 Guided Work-Instruction Author.
